  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, dependencies (tasks 040 + 041 + 042 + 052) marked ✅ in `TASK-INDEX.md`. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;` — especially spec.md FR-20, design.md §5 (IGateResolver), and the `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` from task 042.</step>
    <step order="2">Use the `jps-action-create` skill to scaffold the Template JSON. Populate:
      - `instruction`: brief LLM-facing description (used if the Template is also discoverable via FindResources for ad-hoc invocation)
      - `scopes`: `[{name: "matterId", type: "guid", required: true}, {name: "recipients", type: "stringArray", required: true, sourceHints: ["matter.outsideCounsel", "ask"]}]`
      - `templateParams`: `[{name: "dayOfWeek", type: "enum", values: ["MON","TUE","WED","THU","FRI","SAT","SUN"], default: "MON"}, {name: "timeOfDay", type: "string", default: "09:00"}, {name: "lookaheadDays", type: "int", default: 7}, {name: "humanGateOverride", type: "bool", default: true}]`
      - `trigger`: `{type: "scheduled", cronExpression: "0 {timeOfDayHour} * * {dayOfWeek}"}` (Hybrid D runtime: scheduler from task 001 → SB message → `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler`)
      - `steps`:
        - Step 1: `{tool: "QueryDataverse", params: {entity: "sprk_task", matter: "{matterId}", dueWithinDays: "{lookaheadDays}", status: "open"}}` — Deterministic
        - Step 2: `{tool: "RenderTemplate", params: {templateName: "weekly-task-digest-email", data: "{step1.output}"}}` — Deterministic
        - Step 3: `{tool: "SendEmail", params: {recipients: "{recipients}", subject: "Weekly Task Digest — {matterName}", body: "{step2.output}"}, humanGate: {required: "{humanGateOverride}", gateType: "FinalDelivery", approvalRoles: ["matterPartner", "matterPM"], defaultResolver: "InteractiveInChatGateResolver", fallbackResolver: "DataverseQueueGateResolver", timeoutMinutes: 5}}`
      - `output`: `{emailSent: bool, emailMessageId: string, gateOutcome: enum, taskCount: int}`
      - `idempotencyKey`: `"weekly-task-digest:{instanceId}:{cronFireTimeUtc}"`
      - `governance.featureFlag`: `"feature.actionEngine.template.weeklyTaskDigest"`
    </step>
    <step order="3">Run `jps-validate` skill. Halt and fix on schema violations.</step>
    <step order="4">Deploy via `scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1` (or equivalent): upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row keyed by `sprk_name = 'weekly-task-digest'`. Capture stdout/stderr.</step>
    <step order="5">**Test Instance** — create a test `sprk_actioninstance` pointing at a dev Matter with `dayOfWeek=$(today)`, `timeOfDay=$(now + 2 minutes)`, `humanGateOverride=false` (test bypass). The Instance triggers the cron schedule.</step>
    <step order="6">**Scheduled-dispatch verification** — wait for the cron fire (≤2 min). Confirm:
      - The Azure-native scheduler (per task 001's choice — Logic Apps timer / SB scheduled / Functions timer) publishes the dispatch message
      - `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` (task 042) consumes it
      - A `sprk_actionrun` row exists with status `Completed` (or `Failed` with diagnostic info)
      - Step 1 audit (QueryDataverse), Step 2 audit (RenderTemplate), Step 3 audit (SendEmail) all present
      - Email NOT sent for real (dev-mode SendEmail Tool logs to App Insights instead — coordinate with task 044's Tool impl)
      - `IdempotencyKey` recorded on the run; second cron-fire message (if any) MUST be deduplicated
    </step>
    <step order="7">**Gate verification** — create a SECOND test Instance with `humanGateOverride=true`. Trigger the cron. Confirm:
      - Run pauses at Step 3 (SendEmail with gate)
      - Either: `sprk_gate_approval` record created (DataverseQueueGateResolver path) OR an in-chat card appears in SpaarkeAi for the test user (InteractiveInChatGateResolver path) — depending on the resolver selected
      - Approval flow: approve the gate via the resolver's surface → run resumes → email logged
      - Rejection / timeout: separate test, verify run terminates with reason
    </step>
    <step order="8">**Idempotency verification**: synthesize a duplicate dispatch message (or re-fire the cron). Confirm exactly one `sprk_actionrun` row exists for the same `IdempotencyKey` (no duplicate).</step>
    <step order="9">Capture all verification evidence in `notes/deploys/054-template-weekly-task-digest.md`.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md`; checkpoint via `context-handoff`. Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 054 ✅. If deviations, document in `notes/handoffs/054-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="jps-action-create">Scaffold the JPS Action JSON</tool>
    <tool name="jps-validate">Validate JSON against JPS schema</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row</tool>
    <tool name="powershell">Run Seed-JpsActions.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="curl">Invoke BFF endpoints for instance creation / verification</tool>
    <tool name="azure-cli">Inspect scheduler state for verification</tool>
  </tools>

