    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/current-task.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`infra/insights/schemas/template-weekly-task-digest.json` exists and passes `jps-validate`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's `trigger` block declares `type: "scheduled"` with a cron-expression template referencing `{dayOfWeek}` + `{timeOfDay}` parameters.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The `SendEmail` step has `humanGate.required = "{humanGateOverride}"` (parametric, defaulting to true) and `humanGate.gateType = "FinalDelivery"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template declares `idempotencyKey = "weekly-task-digest:{instanceId}:{cronFireTimeUtc}"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After deployment, exactly one `sprk_actiontemplate` row with `sprk_name='weekly-task-digest'` exists. Re-running the seed yields no duplicate.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Scheduled-dispatch path verified**: cron fire → scheduler → `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` → BFF orchestration → run completed. All audit rows present. Evidence in `notes/deploys/054-*.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Gate-pause path verified**: with `humanGateOverride=true`, run pauses at SendEmail; gate approval / rejection / 5-min timeout all behave per ADR-004 + design.md §5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Idempotency verified**: duplicate dispatch message yields exactly one run record (no duplicate).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Recipient is hashed in Tier 2 audit (not plaintext) — ADR-015 compliance.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta zero.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The verification depends on task 042's `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` being functional and the task 001 scheduler being deployed in the dev environment. If those aren't ready, mark this task `blocked` and surface the dependency. Do NOT author the Template against a non-functional scheduler — verification is part of the Template's acceptance.

    The `SendEmail` Tool's dev-mode behavior (log instead of send) is a Tool implementation concern, not a Template concern. Verify via task 044's `SendEmail` Tool that the dev environment is configured to log+suppress rather than send-real-emails. If real emails would send in dev, halt and escalate.

    The two acceptable resolvers (`InteractiveInChatGateResolver` for chat-originated, `DataverseQueueGateResolver` for cron-originated) are both built in Phase 3 (tasks 031 + 032). The Template DECLARES both as acceptable; the BFF orchestrator selects at runtime based on `invocationSurface` field on the Run record.

    Per design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #4 (`IGateResolver` before side effects): the `SendEmail` step's `humanGate.required = true` is the canonical example. Even if the user overrides via Instance parameter, the override is logged per spec.md FR-20 acceptance.

    The cron expression rendering (`0 {timeOfDayHour} * * {dayOfWeek}`) MUST handle the `timeOfDay` parameter format. If `timeOfDay = "09:00"`, the hour is `09`. A small render helper (in the orchestrator from task 041) handles this — confirm the helper exists; if not, file a dependency note.
  </notes>

